				<p>
					Cloud computing in simple terms can be defined as “The on-demand availability of computer system resources, especially data 						storage and computing power.” Cloud computing is a service that was only used by larger companies before, now anyone can access a cloud computer from anywhere in the world.
				</p>

				<p>
					Cloud Computing has taken a serious rise in terms of popularity during the COVID – 19 pandemic, the popularity increased as office 					   workers have been provided with cloud computers as a means to compensate for the lack of hardware power when working from home. A 					 lot of companies and personnel have looked to cloud computing as a solution that can provide server-grade hardware access to 							anyone at home with a good enough internet connection and a pre-existing computer device.

				</p>
